status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
The ultimate reason of this issue:

  • fabric is created
  • fabric-configadmin-bridge (FCAB) is activated
  • FCAB schedules CM updates of PIDs found in profiles
  • among others: org.ops4j.pax.web
  • if ARQ test creates fabric again (with --clean), SCR components are deactivated and activated again
  • during deactivation, ProfileUrlHandler and FabricServiceImpl are deactivated too
  • FCAB-scheduled updates are not stopped and org.ops4j.pax.web.service.jetty.internal.ServerControllerImpl.configure() may fail because profile:jetty.xml was not correctly resolved when configuring Jetty. Either with the above exception ("java.lang.IllegalStateException: Client is not started") or, when ProfileUrlHandler is unregistered, "java.lang.IllegalStateException: Unknown protocol: profile"
  • during next fabric:create, FCAB doesn not schedule CM update for org.ops4j.pax.web PID, because it's not changed!
  • jetty no longer listens on 8181.
After many hours of log grepping, I've added a bunch of synchronizations to ZK/SCR/Configadmin and this error can finally be treated as resolved.
Both mentioned tests seem to run every time (approx. 20 times, no failure detected), so closing this issue. Verified by QE with 6.3.0. v015
